<HL>    Harsco Appoints Finance Chief </HL>
<DD> 04/06/94 </DD>
<SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B9 </SO>
<CO>    HSC </CO>
<IN> DIVERSIFIED INDUSTRIAL (IDD) </IN>
<DATELINE> CAMP HILL, Pa. </DATELINE>
<TXT>
<p>
   Harsco Corp. named Leonard A. Campanaro, senior
vice president of finance, to the additional post of chief financial
officer. He had been performing the duties of finance chief, but
didn't hold the title, said a spokeswoman for the company. Mr.
Campanaro, 45 years old, also was named to serve on the newly formed
senior management committee of this diversified industrial
manufacturing and service concern.
</p>
<p>
   Harsco assigned three other executives to new jobs and to the new
committee. Paul C. Coppock, 43, was named senior vice president,
general counsel, secretary and chief administrative officer, a new
post. William D. Etzweiler, 58, was named senior vice president and
chief operating officer of commercial and industrial products.
Barrett W. Taussig, 54, was named senior vice president and chief
operating officer of defense.
</p>
